problem.markdown:
We define a new module, which takes as input a vector [x1, x2, x3, x4, x5, x6] and gives an output [y1, y2, y3].

The forward method is defined as:
\(y1 = ReLU(x1+x2)\)
\(y2 = ReLU(x3+x4)\)
\(y3 = ReLU(x5+x6)\)

>>Identify the entries that can be non-zeros of the <a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Jacobian_matrix_and_determinant" target="blank">Jacobian</a>
 in grey.<<

